This paper is primarily focused on the legal and regulatory aspects of AI, which suggests that it would likely be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper discusses the need for precise definitions and the use of a risk-based approach, which are both relevant to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also touches on issues related to cybersecurity (cs.CY) and privacy (cs.CR), which are important considerations in the development and regulation of AI systems. Finally, the paper discusses the use of natural language processing (NLP) in legal definitions, which is relevant to the sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language).
